lly for the active dynamic-access class, and I could name it `VfsUtilsTest`. Finally, I need to ensure the include files are changed and that tests are run correctly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented dedicated coverage for `org.springframework.core.io.VfsUtils`.\n\nChanged files:\n- Added `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_core/VfsUtilsTest.java`\n  - Exercises `VfsResource` public APIs that initialize and invoke `VfsUtils`.\n  - Covers file-backed VFS operations and relative resource resolution.\n- Added minimal test-scope JBoss VFS API stubs:\n  - `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/src/test/java/org/jboss/vfs/VFS.java`\n  - `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/src/test/java/org/jboss/vfs/VirtualFile.java`\n  - `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/src/test/java/org/jboss/vfs/VirtualFileVisitor.java`\n  - `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/src/test/java/org/jboss/vfs/VisitorAttributes.java`\n\nNotes:\n- The new test reaches `VfsUtils` through Spring’s public `VfsResource` API.\n- No direct reflection is used in the tests.\n- I did not compile or run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03aeb5b55a575e260169f588153ee4819f9865ddea4d489c39\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 451, "output": 1290, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32461, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777698820492, "responseId": "resp_03aeb5b55a575e260169f58804f5a4819fb19587180bbe2a0a"}}
